<span id="freeTextContainer625326473953755985"><u>2 Bad Day ★&apos;s</u> <br/><br/><i>
  <b>“It was a terrible, horrible, no good, very bad day.”</b>
</i><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1551341957i/27128888._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I read this to my little niece the other day, let&apos;s just say we weren&apos;t very impressed by this book. I get the meaning behind it and it&apos;s true sometimes you just have a Terrible, Horrible, No Good, Very Bad Day. Days where one thing after another go wrong and it puts you in a terrible mood but... still, I didn&apos;t like the overall negative feeling of this book. Really Alexander just came across as a little brat and was a bit an</span>
  <span id="freeText625326473953755985" style="display:none"><u>2 Bad Day ★'s</u> <br><br><i>
  <b>“It was a terrible, horrible, no good, very bad day.”</b>
</i><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1551341957i/27128888._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I read this to my little niece the other day, let's just say we weren't very impressed by this book. I get the meaning behind it and it's true sometimes you just have a Terrible, Horrible, No Good, Very Bad Day. Days where one thing after another go wrong and it puts you in a terrible mood but... still, I didn't like the overall negative feeling of this book. Really Alexander just came across as a little brat and was a bit annoying at times. I certainly won't be reading this one again and It's not one I'll be recommending either. It's just not for us! <br><br><b>
  <i>“Some days are like that. Even in Australia.”</i>
